Function to split to csv files for independent analyses.

csvSplit.Rd

Function to split to csv files for independent analyses.

Usage

csvSplit(
  data,
  split_data_name,
  time_split,
  date_format = c("%m-%d-%Y %H:%M:%S", "GMT"),
  split = FALSE,
  N_Ch = 4
)

Arguments

data

The data file that needs to be split (this is after the raw file .txt/.xlsx/.csv conversion to data-analysis csv file)

split_data_name

Some unique names string for the new files (two files split at the indicated time)

time_split

Time at which the split should happen (in minutes)

date_format

Common format of from the CSV conversion.

split

Logical, if TRUE, the two new files will be saved; if FALSE the plot for visualization of the split will be saved, but the data will not.

N_Ch

The number of channels in the csv file. It must be either 4 or 8. 8-Channel oxygen meter has 4 temperature and 4 oxygen sensors. The microplate reader files have 4 at this step.

Value

The output from print
